Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Pop the @cauliflower florets{300%g} onto a #baking tray{} and scatter over the @Thai style spice mix{1}. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and @ground black pepper{}. Toss well to combine and place in a single layer on a baking tray. Roast on the top shelf of your #oven until golden and tender, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Chop the @mangetout{80%g} in half widthways. Zest and halve the @lime{1}(zested and halved). Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #colander. Finely chop the @salted peanuts{25%g} or use the base of a #pan to crush them. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat. When hot add the @Red Thai Style Paste{75%g} and cook stirring frequently until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add the garlic and @ginger puree{1%tsp} and cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Add the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @water{100%ml} for the curry. Season with salt and pepper, bring to the boil and add the chickpeas and mangetout. Simmer until slightly thickened and the mangetout is tender, ~{3-4%mins}.

Carefully fluff up the rice using a #fork. Stir through the lime zest and half the coriander.

Add a squeeze of lime juice to the curry, taste and season with salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Cut any remaining lime into wedges. Share the rice between #bowls. Top with the chickpea curry. Place the roasted cauliflower on top, sprinkle over the peanuts and coriander. Serve with lime wedges along side. Enjoy!